s on nuclear plants and the rapid spread of computer technology putting new =
demands on the grid, Congress opted for a competitive market. The plan was t=
o dismantle long-standing utility monopolies and replace them with innovativ=
e electricity companies responsive to the laws of supply and demand.=20
