l engineering" than was required in other commodity businesses, Skilling sai=
d. By the late 1990s, Enron was buying the output of generating plants days,=
 weeks, months and even years before it was produced, using sophisticated we=
ather and economic data to predict a price at which it could be profitably s=
old.=20
