ng companies. Its net income rose 40 percent in the second quarter of this y=
ear, although the price of a share has sunk to less than half of its 2000 hi=
gh of $90, mainly because of setbacks in businesses unrelated to electricity=
=2E Investors pushed the price still lower after Skilling's departure last w=
eek.=20
