=2E's affiliate, said he was not happy about the way FERC was proceeding.=20
"I'm opposed to any [changes to] our electric system in Alabama until I know=
 it's going to bring rates down and enhance reliability for us," he said.=20
In the view of Southern Co. Chairman Franklin, it is still an "open question=
" whether FERC has the legal authority to force utilities to surrender contr=
ol of all their wires.=20
Nonetheless, the restructuring of the power markets may already have gone to=
o far to "put the genie back in the bottle," according to a former FERC offi=
cial.=20
The power merchants readily concur.=20
"Everybody's paying too much because you've got this huge conservatism built=
